               <p>RICHARD SMART. I have a stable in <placeName id="t18270913-217-crimeloc1229">Barnsbury-mews, lslington</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-217-crimeloc1229" type="placeName" value="Barnsbury-mews, lslington"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-217-crimeloc1229" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-217-off1227 t18270913-217-crimeloc1229"></join>. On the 5th of September, I went there, and missed this pipe and cock, which served the stable with water.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-217-person1912">
                  JOHN 
                  ELEMENT
               <interp inst="t18270913-217-person1912" type="surname" value="ELEMENT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-217-person1912" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-217-person1912" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman of lslington. I was in Barnsbury mews. Lane called me, and said the prisoner had got a parcel of lead - I took him to the watch-house with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-217-person1913">
                  SAMUEL 
                  LANE
               <interp inst="t18270913-217-person1913" type="surname" value="LANE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-217-person1913" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-217-person1913" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I stopped the prisoner on the 5th of September, with a basket of lead in his hand - he put it down by his side - another person was with him; the prisoner denied having it, but I saw it in his hand - he was within six yards of the stable.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-217-person1914">
                  THOMAS 
                  GRAFTON
               <interp inst="t18270913-217-person1914" type="surname" value="GRAFTON"></interp>
